ce:section.ce:para:
In addition to the degradation experiments, scavenger radical studies were executed to ascertain the nature of the active radical species which might be responsible for the photocatalytic decomposition of IC dye (Fig. 6c). Different scavengers including K2Cr2O7 (scavenger for electrons; e−), NaCl (scavenger for holes; h+) and IPA (scavenger of hydroxyl radicals; 

                        OH) were investigated for this purpose. The photocatalytic degradation of the dye without any scavenger was 86% and this decreased to 58%, 59% and 80% in the presence of IPA, K2Cr2O7 and NaCl, respectively. The results obtained demonstrate that 

                        OH and e− are dominating and are the primary reactive species in the photocatalytic decomposition of IC dye.
